@Deliriumgoddess6: Uhm, you shouldn't have pasted it all, it's not wise speaking of privacy. Anyway, it seems you are running Tor from the Tor Browser Bundle; I run tor as a standalone and it doesn't use port 9151 for the `ControlPort`  but yours does. I think you should check your `/etc/zeronet.conf` file, and ensure you have something like this.
`tor_controller = 127.0.0.1:9151`
`tor_proxy = 127.0.0.1:9050`
